# Architecture – layers

## Data flow

```text
MCP (analysis / UI understanding / suggestions)
  → Skills (reusable workflows, contracts)
  → Playwright tests (deterministic execution via CLI)
  → Reports (Markdown / HTML from Playwright + summaries)
```

## Folder roles

| Path | Role |
|------|------|
| `src/core/` | Shared types, small orchestration helpers (no browser I/O). |
| `src/skills/` | Code backing for skill contracts when needed (keep thin). |
| `src/services/` | External integrations (API clients, file I/O helpers). |
| `src/reporting/` | Report builders, merge CLI output with narrative summaries. |
| `tests/e2e/` | UI tests only. |
| `tests/api/` | API tests only. |
| `tests/plans/` | Generated or hand-written test plans. |
| `tests/seed.spec.ts` | Demo seed file (keep path stable for agent examples). |
| `reports/` | Generated reports for demos and CI artifacts as needed. |

## Anti-patterns

- Clicking or typing through MCP to “run” a test case instead of running `npx playwright test`.
- Putting non-deterministic AI execution inside `tests/**/*.spec.ts`.
- Mixing “plan” and “execute” in the same artifact without a clear boundary.
